programme.title: PL Stories: Reggae Rhythms in the Premier League
programme.desc: Reggae Rhythms in the Premier League explores the powerful connection between Jamaica and the world’s most-watched football league, showcasing how the island’s culture, music, and style have influenced the Premier League. We feature iconic Jamaican players who have left their mark, while also diving into the impact of reggae music, fashion, and fan culture on the game. Through exclusive interviews and untold stories, we see how Jamaican heritage has shaped both football and broader global culture, from the pitch to the streets.

programme.title: The Big Interview: Emile Smith Rowe
programme.desc: He was a Gunner through and through, from academy level to the first team, Emile Smith Rowe lived his dream of playing for Arsenal, the club he grew up supporting. Now at Fulham and injury-free, the 24-year-old is enjoying a new lease of life in West London. In this week’s Big Interview, Smith Rowe talks about his journey from grassroots to becoming a pro, what his parents had to sacrifice to help achieve his dream, as well as the difficult decision to leave Arsenal to further his career.
